This place is a lot of fun!!!

It is also one of the biggest entertainment bargains in the city.

Range prices vary a little based on the time of day but they are very reasonable.

Food and beverages are not only tasty but the prices are very reasonable and in line with most casual restaurants around town. the pickle fries are so addictive and we always get a flatbread to share, and draft beers are $4 -$6 bucks

The place is run by real pro's because everyone knows how to take care of you, from getting signed in or learning how to play a game or bringing your drinks promptly with a big smile.

You don't have to be a golfer to have a great time, and I recommend The top 2 levels for that unique driving range experience.